-- Ski-Doo snowmobiles maker BRP posts quarterly net loss
-- By Anannya Pramanick in Bangalore
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 07:29AM EDT
-- None



March 28 (Reuters) - BRP Inc <DOO.TO>, the maker of Ski-Doo snowmobiles and Sea-Doo watercraft, posted a quarterly net loss, mainly due to higher expenses.

The company, which was spun off from Bombardier Inc <BBDb.TO> in 2003, reported a net loss of C$6.3 million ($5.7 million) for the quarter ended Jan. 31 compared with a profit of C$35.8 million, a year earlier. [ID:nCNWKdLKZa] BRP earned 41 Canadian cents per share, excluding items.